main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects reported in Williston, Florida between 1955 and 1956.
interesting points: Air traffic control radar operators observed three round objects which changed altitude and speed,The objects were described as circular and larger than the witness's aircraft, resembling a refueling operation caused multiple reports of flying saucers in the area, Witnesses included police and air traffic controllers who claimed the objects made no sound or vapor trail, One report detailed that a policeman experienced a tingling sensation while observing a UFO hover above a police car.
sighted object: three round objects and several white oval-shaped objects
witness description: Air traffic control radar operators and police officers
